parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the EPS system can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose steering control, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel pulls to the left or right
the vehicle veers off course
the steering wheel feels loose or soft
the vehicle is difficult to control
especially at high speeds
the EPS warning light illuminates
and the vehicle may jerk or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or rattles
difficulty controlling the vehicle
especially at high speeds
the steering column makes a loud humming or grinding sound
and the vehicle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The power steering light flickers on and off
the radio and lights turn off while driving
the vehicle is difficult to turn
especially at low speeds
and the steering wheel feels heavy or hard to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to shudder or vibrate, leading to loss of power and acceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Shuddering or vibrating when accelerating
loss of power
hesitation when shifting gears
rough ride
and clicking or grinding noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Transmission slipping or hesitation
loss of power
hesitation when shifting gears
rough ride
and clicking or grinding noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake failure
sudden acceleration
and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
loud grinding or clanking noise when applying brakes
brake warning light stays on
"Check Brake System" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to fail to stop or slow down, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle fails to stop or slow down
brake pedal goes to the floor
loud grinding or clanking noise when applying brakes
brake warning light stays on
"Check Brake System" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
loud grinding or clanking noise when applying brakes
brake warning light stays on
"Check Brake System" message appears on the dashboard.
